Enzymes are biological catalysts that lower the activation energy of a reaction  allowing a more efficient pathway for the reaction to take place. The formation of an enzyme-substrate complex lowers the activation energy. There are 4 ways in which an enzyme-substrate complex lowers activation energy:proximity effect  strain effect  orientation effect and microenvironment effect.There are 2 models of enzymatic action  the lock and key hypothesis and the induced fit hypothesis.
